The paper deals with saliency prediction for mobile user interfaces, which involves analyzing the elements of the interface such as buttons and text. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category, which deals with image analysis and recognition. Additionally, the paper involves collecting eye-gaze data from mobile devices, which suggests that it may also belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The paper also involves developing a deep learning model, which suggests that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper may also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category, as it involves predicting saliency in images, and the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category, as it deals with analyzing images in the context of mobile user interfaces.
